<h2>Cosmic Horror Warlock</h2>

<p><strong>Class:</strong> Warlock (Great Old One)</p>
<p><strong>Race:</strong> Wood Half-Elf (preferred, but any race is viable)</p>
<p><strong>Background:</strong> Charlatan</p>

<h3>Stats</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Start:</strong> STR 8, DEX 16 (15+1), CON 14, INT 10, WIS 8, CHA 17 (15+2)</li>
    <li><strong>Endgame:</strong> STR 8, DEX 16, CON 14, INT 10, WIS 8, CHA 20</li>
</ul>

<h3>Build Summary</h3>
<p>
    This build revolves around maximizing <strong>Eldritch Blast</strong> damage and exploiting critical hit synergy. With 20 Charisma and key gear, you’ll hit for <strong>3d10 + 30</strong> per turn at level 10. By stacking crit range bonuses, you’ll reach <strong>14–20</strong> crit range late-game. The Great Old One subclass synergizes with crits by applying AoE <em>Frightened</em> on crits.
</p>

<h3>Character Creation</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Race/Subrace:</strong> Wood Half-Elf (for Shield proficiency, Stealth, charm/sleep resistance)</li>
    <li><strong>Class:</strong> Warlock</li>
    <li><strong>Subclass:</strong> The Great Old One</li>
    <li><strong>Background:</strong> Charlatan</li>
    <li><strong>Cantrips:</strong> Eldritch Blast, Mage Hand</li>
    <li><strong>Spells:</strong> Hex, Dissonant Whispers</li>
    <li><strong>Skills:</strong> Deception, Sleight of Hand, Stealth, Intimidation, Investigation</li>
</ul>

<h3>Feats</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Level 4:</strong> +2 Charisma (to 19)</li>
    <li><strong>Level 8:</strong> Spell Sniper (+1 crit range)</li>
    <li><strong>Level 12:</strong> Optional — Alert, Actor, or +2 Charisma</li>
</ul>
<p>
    You can reach 20 Charisma early by making a deal with Auntie Ethel in Act 1. It fits the theme and boosts power early. If not, Actor is a viable alternative for Charisma and deception.
</p>

<h3>Pact Choice</h3>
<p>
    <strong>Pact of the Chain</strong> is the best fit. Blade and Tome offer no synergy here. The familiar adds battlefield utility, even if weak.
</p>

<h3>Eldritch Invocations</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Level 2:</strong> Agonizing Blast*, Repelling Blast*</li>
    <li><strong>Level 5:</strong> Devil’s Sight*</li>
    <li><strong>Level 7:</strong> One With Shadows</li>
    <li><strong>Level 9:</strong> Beguiling Influence</li>
    <li><strong>Level 12:</strong> Minions of Chaos</li>
</ul>

<h3>Spell Priorities</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Core:</strong> Eldritch Blast, Hex, Darkness</li>
    <li><strong>Utility:</strong> Misty Step, Detect Thoughts, Dimension Door, Telekinesis</li>
</ul>

<h3>Equipment</h3>
<p>
    Most gear is available by Act 2. You won’t attack with weapons — they’re stat sticks. Proficiency doesn’t matter.
</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Knife of the Undermountain King:</strong> +1 crit range (Crèche Y’llek)</li>
    <li><strong>Bow of the Banshee:</strong> +1d4 to attack rolls vs Frightened (Grymforge)</li>
    <li><strong>The Dead Shot:</strong> +1 crit range (Act 3, Lower City)</li>
    <li><strong>Potent Robe:</strong> Adds Charisma to cantrip damage, +1 AC, bonus HP (Act 2)</li>
    <li><strong>Covert Cowl:</strong> +1 crit range while obscured (Last Light Inn)</li>
    <li><strong>Risky Ring:</strong> Advantage on attacks, Disadvantage on saves (Moonrise Towers)</li>
    <li><strong>Disintegrating Night Walkers:</strong> Misty Step, immunity to terrain effects (Grymforge)</li>
    <li><strong>Daredevil Gloves:</strong> +1 spell attack, ignore melee casting penalties (Crèche Y’llek)</li>
    <li><strong>Ketheric’s Shield:</strong> +1 spell save DC and spell attack (Act 2)</li>
    <li><strong>Shade-Slayer Cloak:</strong> +1 crit range while hiding (Thieves’ Guild, Act 3)</li>
    <li><strong>Bloodthirst:</strong> +1 crit range, +1 AC in off-hand (Orin, Act 3)</li>
    <li><strong>Elixir of Viciousness:</strong> +1 crit range (craftable, Act 2)</li>
</ul>